unit.doc: Module type signatures for Cohttp components

module_type.doc: The IO module defines the blocking interface for reading and writing to Cohttp streams

type.doc: 'a t represents a blocking monad state

value.doc: a >>= b will pass the result of a to the b function. This is a monadic bind.
return a will construct a constant IO value.

type.doc: conn represents the underlying network flow

value.doc: iter f l will perform a blocking iteration using f over the l list. The result is determined after all the iterating threads have completed in serial.
read_line ic will read a single line terminated by CR or CRLF from the input channel ic. It returns optionNone if EOF or other error condition is reached.

read ic len will block until a maximum of len characters are read from the input channel ic. It returns an empty string if EOF or some other error condition occurs on the input channel, and can also fewer than len if input buffering is not sufficient to satisfy the request.
read_exactly ic len will block until exactly len characters are read from the input channel ic. If EOF or some other error condition is reached, then optionNone is returned.
write oc s will block until the complete s string is written to the output channel oc.
flush oc will return when all previously buffered content from calling SIOwrite have been written to the output channel oc.
